Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm chunks.

Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

When boiling, pour the water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{} with
@salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @basmati rice{150%grams} and cook for
~{10-12%mins}.

When cooked, drain in a sieve and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{}
and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%grams} and pepper chunks and stir-fry until
the chorizo starts to brown, ~{3-4%mins}.

Add the @Mexican style spice mix{1%sachet} to your pan. Cook, stirring, for
~{1%min}.

Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}, @finely chopped tomatoes with onion
and garlic{1%carton}, @chipotle paste{20%grams} and kidney beans (add less
chipotle if you prefer things milder) along with the @sugar{1%tsp}.

Bring to the boil and stir to combine. Lower the heat and simmer until
thickened, ~{5-6%mins}.

Once thickened, stir the @baby spinach{40%grams} through the chilli a handful
at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of @water{} to loosen if
you'd like.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then serve in #bowls{} topped with the chipotle
bean chilli.

Add a spoonful of @soured cream{50%grams} to finish.

> This Chipotle Bean and Chorizo Chilli is bursting full of flavours and makes the
> perfect dinner night option from HelloFresh. Cook up a fresh start!